(firstQuint)An Early Access Programme for Moxetumomab Pasudotox in Relapsed/Refractory Hairy Cell Leukemia.

 Multicentre Early Access Programme, designed to provide treatment access to moxetumomab pasudotox for eligible patients with relapsed/refractory hairy cell leukemia who are at least 18 years of age, have adequate organ function and are Pseudomonas-immunotoxin naive.

 Patients will be administered moxetumomab pasudotox on Days 1, 3 and 5 of each 28-day cycle until documentation of CR or for up to 6 cycles, progressive disease (PD), initiation of alternate therapy or unacceptable toxicity.

